Where Clause
-------
where clause we can use to filter 1 row and it will use before group by clause and one more thing in where clause we can't use aggregate functions (SUM, COUNT, AVG, etc.)?
syntax: SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEES WHERE SALARY > 40000;

Having 
--------
having  we can use to filter group of rows and it will use after group by clause ,in having clause we can use aggregate functions (SUM, COUNT, AVG, etc.)?
syntax:SELECT DEPARTMENT,AVG(SALARY) FROM EMPLOYEES GROUP BY DEPARTMENT HAVING AVG(SALARY) >40000
